Hitting Baghdad where it hurts, more countries have

joined a U.N.-sanctioned boycott of oil from Iraq and Kuwait.
More than 90 percent of imports from Iraq to the 12-nation EEC are petroleum products.
The EEC also suspended arms sales to Iraq.
In addition, Switzerland prohibited all payments and other financial transfers to Iraq and Kuwait.
Japan imports 99 percent of its oil.
Wholesale oil prices soared to five-year highs in New York on Monday.
France will introduce controls Thursday on prices of petroleum products to prevent refiners from using Iraq's invasion of Kuwait as an excuse to raise prices, acting Premier Pierre Beregovoy announced Tuesday.
